Description:
Silos Sensation
Tucked inside the iconic Islington Silos complex, with its fabulous communal areas and gym, this modern apartment is sure to make an impression with its quality interior and top Collingwood location.
Featuring open floor plan, well-appointed kitchen with stainless steel cooking appliances and the lounge/dining area opening out to a full-width outdoor terrace. Other highlights include ducted heating/cooling, quality carpets and flooring, European laundry, video intercom/secure entry, plus undercover parking space.
Perfectly positioned only walking distance to Victoria Parade trams, Collingwood Station as well as both Victoria & Smith Street's endless array of shops, cafes, restaurants bars and boutiques. This apartment is a great opportunity to start, add to the portfolio, or move on in to experience Collingwood at it's best.
Insights: 11/55 Islington Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Quality Exudes from The Modest Industrial Entry Onwards…
Within the historic Silo Apartments where four cylindrical concrete towers mark the central focus of the development and situated in the still industrial sector of Collingwood, you’ll enter through a large copperised swing door to the central forecourt with BBQ area and a number of relaxation spots. This first floor apartment has a spacious one bedroom design with larger than usual balcony and a fully blown kitchen instead of the tiny kitchenette’s in most apartments. Overlooking Islington St its private enough but encapsulates the inner city hub of activity.
Security entry, single car stacker, storage cage and long standing lessee make this an ideal investment, or for the owner occupier we’ll have to give our lessee the bad news and find them a new home such is their cailbre.
Insights: 104/55 Islington Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 49 other 1 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Spectacular warehouse conversion with X-factor luxury
A state-of-the-art brilliantly executed design by CHT Architects, this compelling multi-level warehouse conversion features a suspended showcase garage to allow yourself the luxury of vast and versatile, direct drive-in living. This innovative apartment is absolutely spectacular blending its Foy & Gibson industrial heritage with outstanding modern style and cutting-edge quality.
Secluded on the ground-floor with direct Street access, this amazing contemporary residence meets all aspirations for sensational city-edge success. Authentic original brickwork and steel beams frame a cleverly balanced interior revolving around a spacious open-plan living and dining zone. The layout offers 2 or 3 bedrooms including main with atrium, ensuite, dressing room and backlit display case cellar. There's a light-filled mezzanine lounge area (gas fireplace) and sleek chef's kitchen with in-situ concrete benchtop, butler's pantry and Miele coffee machine. Also boasts library/sitting area, 2 bathrooms, laundry, C-BUS, alarm and heating/cooling near exciting Smith & Gertrude Streets.
Insights: 8/93 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Victorian vision meets contemporary cool
A fashionable three bedroom, two bathroom base in an irresistible position, this renovated and extended double fronted Victorian makes all the right impressions and opens the door to a fantastic lifestyle seconds to vibrant Smith Street. Light-filled, spacious and open, the first floor living/dining/kitchen features a soaring vaulted ceiling, polished floorboards, suite of stainless steel Bosch appliances, expansive stone surfaces and tall sliding glass door to a paved terrace. Three double bedrooms each offer a built-in or walk-through robe, bathrooms include an ensuite, and on a superb list of extras you'll find a powder room/laundry, heating/cooling, central vacuum, solar hot water, storage and auto double garage with internal access. Trams, bars, cafes and restaurants are all a stroll away.
Insights: 34 Keele Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 24 other 3 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Make your Marque
Embrace inner-city living from the seclusion of your own balcony. This first-floor apartment is secure, stylish and serene. Seconds from Smith Street, get your mornings rolling across the road at Proud Mary. Wind down in the evening at your pick of the boutique bars on Gertrude Street. Owner-occupied and offered for the first time, this modern apartment features entrance hallway, 1 double bedroom with built-in robes, study alcove, smart living/dining room spilling onto a superb balcony, gourmet stone kitchen, bathroom with laundry area, heating/cooling, polished timber floors, lift access, storage cupboard and basement car space on title. Marque enjoys access to a sensational communal rooftop terrace.

Description:
Brand New with Sensational City Views
Just completed this stunning Kennedy Nolan designed apartment will appeal to the discerning buyer. Finished with many features and architectural detail this unique property includes a full size kitchen with Miele appliances, large kitchen island bench, pantry, heaps of cupboards and integrated fridge. Both beautiful and functional this clever layout offers a separate study alcove, generous sized bedroom, bathroom with an openable window and rogerseller bathroom fittings. Concrete soffit ceiling allows for high clearance to the living room. Balcony doors open from either side to allow excellent air flow and easy access to the huge balcony and the most spectacular city views. Timber floors, carpet to the bedroom, concealed reverse cycle heating and cooling - no condenser on the balcony. Be the first to live in this designer pad located just off Smith and Gertrude Streets, completed in December 2018 Little Oxford is a boutique building of 29 apartments. Car space and storage cage included.
Insights: 503/9 Little Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 49 other 1 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

One bedroom plus study in Lantern

Best practice conversion design: spacious, secure and well located
Set behind the Deco facade of a former engineering workshop, this immaculate 2-level apartment in a block of only 7 offers exceptionally quiet living minutes from Smith Street bars and cafes and close to Victoria Park Station. Description:
Trendy interiors for irresistible inner-city living
Warehouse inspired, this designer two bedroom townhouse boasts the trendy interiors and premium location that make inner city living irresistible. Private and secure, part of a tightly held complex this property impresses with double height ceilings through open plan living, creating an airy ambience around a rustic timber staircase segregating the living domain into two distinct zones. The chic kitchen with stainless steel appliances and benchtop, a stylish addition to this domain and perfectly placed to service the private decked courtyard. Double bedrooms with BIR's and balcony access share a central spa bathroom while comfort and convenience are assured with heating/cooling and secure gated entry to a covered car space. All adjacent buzzing Smith Street and a short tram trip to the CBD.

Description:
Superb Inner City Living
Set in the highly sought Yorkshire Brewery development superbly located within Collingwood’s renowned coffee scene and surrounded by award winning restaurants on Smith Street & Brunswick Street, this attractive home is a must for any astute investor or owner occupier alike.
Architecturally designed by Hayball Architects, the flowing layout comprises of an open plan living and dining area with direct access to an enclosed terrace with superb views of the CBD & Brew Tower. The stunning kitchen is highlighted by LED back drop lighting, stone bench-tops and soft close cupboards. The functional study with built in desk then leads to a carpeted bedroom with full length built in mirrored robes. The home also features a stylish bathroom, full European laundry, stainless steel appliances and ample storage.
Residents within the Yorkshire Brewery also benefit from an onsite building manager and take advantage of private facilities including gym, library, roof top terrace, dining room & 2 guest suites only available to residents in the complex.
Savvy investors take note this apartment is leased on a periodic tenancy returning over 5.5% pa gross (monthly rental $1,955pcm).
If you have any further questions or would like to inspect, please phone Patrick on 0402 075 501.
Insights: 804E/9 Robert Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 49 other 1 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Top Floor Triumph
Bathe in the afternoon sun and admire the breath-taking uninterrupted views of Melbourne’s CBD skyline from your private terrace in this stunning corner apartment. Situated on the top floor of the Silo building located within the historically preserved Yorkshire Brewery this apartment is conveniently located within Collingwood’s renowned coffee district & only moments from award-winning restaurants and also boasts easy access to the CBD by tram or foot.
Architecturally designed by Hayball Architects, the flowing layout comprises bright open plan living and dining area with direct access to a private north facing balcony. The stunning kitchen is highlighted by LED back drop lighting, stone bench-tops and soft close cupboards. The bedrooms are carpeted and include built in mirrored robes, with the master also boasting an en-suite bathroom. The property also features a second guest bathroom, full European laundry, stainless steel appliances and ample storage.
Residents within the Yorkshire Brewery also benefit from an onsite building manager and take advantage of private facilities including gym, library, roof top terrace, dining room & 2 guest suites only available to residents in the complex.
The property is currently secured on a fixed term lease agreement expiring on the 30/06/2019 returning $2,477 pcm.
If you have any further questions please phone Patrick on 0402 075 501.
Insights: 1306E/9 Robert Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Top Floor - Top Class
Elevated, secluded and boutique this two bedroom 1970's style apartment exudes inner city charm with its appealing location and light filled living. Located on one of Collingwood's best residential street with easy access to Victoria, Gertrude, Smith and Brunswick St - this top floor apartment also boasts an enormous communal roof deck - ideal for entertaining withy stunning city views. Offering a north facing orientation and streaming with natural light the apartment consists of a well sized open plan living area, separate kitchen and meals area's, central bathroom, separate toilet, 2 generously sized bedrooms, separate storage locker and its own lock up garage. The complete inner city package ideal for first home buyers or the astute inner city investor.
